62.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"></picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-credits\">3D_generator</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <h2>Investment Thesis</h2> <p>I am rating Carlisle Companies Incorporated (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CSL\" title=\"Carlisle Companies Incorporated\">CSL</a></span>) a hold due to its neutral price outlook. The stock is trading near its 52-week-high, and it is currently in a dominant sideways movement, signaling a consolidation phase. Looking at its financials, the company</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/520290362/image_520290362.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4743244-carlisle-companies-incorporated-neutral-stock-outlook-amid-business-realignment", "pub_date": "2024-12-10 15:00:01"}, {"id": "4743254", "title": "Wall Street Breakfast Podcast: Taiwan Semi Chips In Big Gains", "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1199346879/image_1199346879.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Company (TSMC) headquarters in Silicon Valley\" data-id=\"1199346879\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"5325px\" height=\"3550px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1199346879/image_1199346879.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1199346879/image_1199346879.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1199346879/image_1199346879.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1199346879/image_1199346879.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1199346879/image_1199346879.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1199346879/image_1199346879.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1199346879/image_1199346879.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1199346879/image_1199346879.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"> </p> <p class=\"item-credits\">Sundry Photography</p></figcaption></figure><div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div></p> <p>Listen below or on the go on <a href=\"https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/wall-street-breakfast/id1358381502?mt=2\" rel=\"nofollow\">Apple Podcasts</a> and <a href=\"https://open.spotify.com/show/05uLjJxkVgQsRk8LWLCLpx?si=r3_yJgxiQiivJwNQG8WNew&amp;nd=1\" rel=\"nofollow\">Spotify</a></p> <p><div class=\"pcast hidden-print\">\n  <div class=\"pcast__section-1\">\n    <img alt=\"\" class=\"pcast__top-img pcast__marketing\" src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2018/11/21/podcast_series_header.png\">\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"pcast__section-2\"><iframe src=\"https://widget.spreaker.com/player?episode_id=63252015&amp;theme=light&amp;playlist=false&amp;playlist-continuous=false&amp;chapters-image=true&amp;episode_image_position=right&amp;hide-logo=true&amp;hide-likes=true&amp;hide-comments=true&amp;hide-sharing=true&amp;hide-download=true&amp;color=ff6900\" width=\"100%\" height=\"200px\" frameborder=\"0\" sap-id=\"4\"></iframe></div>\n  <div class=\"pcast__section-3\">\n    <div class=\"pcast__ad-container\"></div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n</p> <p>Taiwan Semiconductor's (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/TSM\" title=\"Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Company Limited\">TSM</a>) November <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4380732-taiwan-semiconductors-november-revenue-surges-34\">revenue surges</a> 34%. (00:23) The Container Store (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/TCSG\" title=\"The Container Store Group, Inc.\">TCSG</a>) shares to be <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4380151-the-container-store-shares-pulled-from-nyse\">pulled from NYSE</a>. (01:23) Costco (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/COST\" title=\"Costco Wholesale Corporation\">COST</a>) <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4379905-costco-switching-diaper-production-from-kimberly-clark\">switching</a> diaper production from Kimberly-Clark (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/KMB\" title=\"Kimberly-Clark Corporation\">KMB</a>). (02:13)</p> <p>This is an abridged transcript of the podcast.</p> <p>Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing's (NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/TSM#hasComeFromMpArticle=false#source=section%3Amain_content%7Cbutton%3Abody_link%7Cfirst_level_url%3Anews\">TSM</a>) revenue for November <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4380732-taiwan-semiconductors-november-revenue-surges-34\">soared 34%</a> year-over-year to about NT$276.06B.</p> <p>However, revenue for November declined 12.2% compared to October, when the company <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4264735-taiwan-semiconductors-october-revenue-grows-29\">generated</a> NT$314.24B.</p> <p>TSM \u2014 which produces chips for some of the world's largest tech companies including Apple (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/AAPL\" title=\"Apple Inc.\">AAPL</a>), Nvidia (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/NVDA\" title=\"NVIDIA Corporation\">NVDA</a>) and AMD (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/AMD\" title=\"Advanced Micro Devices, Inc.\">AMD</a>) \u2014 <a href=\"https://pr.tsmc.com/system/files/newspdf/attachment/2ebcab972aaa1d72b0596501f04764a2b23f3236/Nov%202024%20%28E%29_final_wmn.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">saw</a> revenue from January through November 2024 amount to NT$2.616T, growing 31.8% compared to the same period in 2023.</p> <p>During TSM's third-quarter <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4168578-taiwan-semi-soars-after-ai-demand-boosts-outlook-q3-results-draw-analysts-praise\">earnings</a> call in October, Chairman and CEO C.C. Wei said that the AI demand was real and that it was just the beginning.</p> <p>Year-to-date, the Taiwan-based company's stock has surged about 91%.</p> <p>TSM is down 1.3% in premarket action.</p> <p>Trading in shares of The Container Store (NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/TCS#hasComeFromMpArticle=false#source=section%3Amain_content%7Cbutton%3Abody_link%7Cfirst_level_url%3Anews\">TCS</a>) have been suspended immediately after the New York Stock Exchange <a href=\"https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20241209673244/en/\" rel=\"nofollow\">said </a>it will begin proceedings to delist the stock from the NYSE.</p> <p>The decision was reached as the company\u2019s global market capitalization had been <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4380151-the-container-store-shares-pulled-from-nyse\">below the $15M threshold</a> for 30 consecutive trading days.</p> <p>The decision is just the latest blow to The Container Store. A potential lifeline from Beyond (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BYON\" title=\"Beyond, Inc.\">BYON</a>) <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4316780-the-container-store-seeks-financing-deal-with-beyond-unravels\">unraveled </a>last month after TCS was unable to satisfy the terms of Beyond\u2019s (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BYON\" title=\"Beyond, Inc.\">BYON</a>) equity investment. Unsuccessful efforts to obtain additional working capital or refinance the terms of its debt raised concerns about the company\u2019s viability and eventually drove shares to an all-time low of $1.79, a loss of 92% from last year.</p> <p>In the<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/pr/19924349-beyond-inc-provides-update-to-investors-regarding-transaction-container-store-group-inc#source=section%3APress%20Releases%7Csection_asset%3APress%20Releases%7Cfirst_level_url%3Asymbol%7Cbutton%3ATitle%7Clock_status%3ANo%7Cline%3A1\"> fiscal second quarter</a>, The Container Store (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/TCS#hasComeFromMpArticle=false#source=section%3Amain_content%7Cbutton%3Abody_link%7Cfirst_level_url%3Anews\">TCS</a>) reported a loss of $3.23 per share (versus a profit of $0.11 a year ago) and a 10.5% drop in sales as comparable store sales fell 12.5% from a year earlier.</p> <p>Kimberly-Clark (NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/KMB#hasComeFromMpArticle=false#source=section%3Amain_content%7Cbutton%3Abody_link%7Cfirst_level_url%3Anews\">KMB</a>) will no longer be making diapers for Costco (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/COST\" title=\"Costco Wholesale Corporation\">COST</a>) as the parent company of Huggies shifts its business model away from <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4379905-costco-switching-diaper-production-from-kimberly-clark\">low-margin private label</a> contracts to higher-priced premium products under its own brand name.</p> <p>According to Bloomberg, Costco (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/COST\" title=\"Costco Wholesale Corporation\">COST</a>) will now sell diapers manufactured by First Quality under its Kirkland Signature brand beginning in January.</p> <p>During its <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4728292-kimberly-clark-corporation-kmb-q3-2024-earnings-call-transcript\">earnings call with analysts</a> in October, Kimberly-Clark CEO Mike Hsu primed investors for this development with Costco (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/COST\" title=\"Costco Wholesale Corporation\">COST</a>), saying that the company would \u201ccease production for a large club private label diaper business\u2026creating a headwind of about 2% next year.\u201d</p> <p>He went on to say that as a result, the company\u2019s private label mix \u201cwill shrink from about 4% in 2023 to about 2% next year,\u201d with the expectation to decline further over time.</p> <p>For Costco (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/COST\" title=\"Costco Wholesale Corporation\">COST</a>), the sale of Kirkland-brand items earns higher margins versus national brands, and appeals to cost-conscious consumers given the slightly lower price point.</p> <p>Kimberly-Clark (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/KMB\" title=\"Kimberly-Clark Corporation\">KMB</a>) shares closed 1.3% lower on Monday but are up 0.6% in premarket trading.</p> <p>More articles on Seeking Alpha:</p> <p><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4380708-boeing-restarts-737-max-production-a-month-after-strike-ends-report\">Boeing restarts 737 MAX production a month after strike ends - report</a></p> <p><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4380720-mcdonalds-review-bombing-google-unitedhealthcare-ceo-murder-suspect-arrest\">McDonald's review bombed on Google after UnitedHealthcare CEO murder suspect's arrest</a></p> <p><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4379647-newell-brands-turnaround-went-unnoticed-investors\">Newell Brands' turnaround went unnoticed by investors - analyst</a></p> <p><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4379519-restaurant-retreat-cava-group-and-sweetgreen-fall-sharply-after-monster-2024-rallies\">Restaurant retreat: CAVA Group and Sweetgreen fall sharply after monster 2024 rallies</a></p> <p>Catalyst watch:</p> <ul> <li><p>Goldman Sachs U.S. Financial Services Conference starts and includes American Express (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/AXP\" title=\"American Express Company\">AXP</a>), Coinbase (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/COIN\" title=\"Coinbase Global, Inc.\">COIN</a>), Blackstone (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BX\" title=\"Blackstone Inc.\">BX</a>), JPMorgan (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/JPM\" title=\"JPMorgan Chase &amp; Co.\">JPM</a>), Blackrock (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BLK\" title=\"BlackRock, Inc.\">BLK</a>), Apollo (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/APO\" title=\"Apollo Global Management, Inc.\">APO</a>), Wells Fargo (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/WFC\" title=\"Wells Fargo &amp; Company\">WFC</a>) and U.S. Bancorp (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/USB\" title=\"U.S. Bancorp\">USB</a>).</p></li> <li><p>The 51st Nasdaq London Investor Conference is scheduled with companies including Akamai (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/AKAM\" title=\"Akamai Technologies, Inc.\">AKAM</a>), Rapid7 (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/RPD\" title=\"Rapid7, Inc.\">RPD</a>), and Western Digital (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/WDC\" title=\"Western Digital Corporation\">WDC</a>).</p></li> <li><p>The UK antitrust regulator's deadline to decide if it will pursue an in-depth probe into SLB's planned purchase of ChampionX (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CHX\" title=\"ChampionX Corporation\">CHX</a>).</p></li> <li><p>JM Smucker (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/SJM\" title=\"The J. M. Smucker Company\">SJM</a>) investor day.</p></li> <li><p>Iqvia (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/IQV\" title=\"IQVIA Holdings Inc.\">IQV</a>) investor day.</p></li> <li><p>A Washington state judge is expected to rule on Kroger's (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/KR\" title=\"The Kroger Co.\">KR</a>) planned takeover of Albertsons (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ACI\" title=\"Albertsons Companies, Inc.\">ACI</a>).</p></li> </ul> <p>Now let\u2019s take a look at the markets as of 6 am. Ahead of the opening bell today, Dow, S&amp;P and Nasdaq futures are in mixed territory. Crude oil is down 1% at $67/barrel. Bitcoin is down 0.4% at $97,000.</p> <p>In the world markets, the FTSE 100 is down 0.6% and the DAX is flat.</p> <p>The <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4380725-biggest-stock-movers-tuesday-orcl-ai-and-more\">biggest movers</a> for the day premarket: Oracle (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ORCL\" title=\"Oracle Corporation\">ORCL</a>) is down more than 8% after reporting lower-than-expected Q2 results.</p> <p>On today\u2019s economic calendar:</p> <ul> <li><p>8:30 am Productivity and Cost</p></li> <li><p>11:00 am Treasury Buyback Announcement</p></li> </ul><div class=\"before_last_paragraph-piano-placeholder\"></div><p>Editor's Note: This article covers one or more microcap stocks. Please be aware of the risks associated with these stocks.</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1199346879/image_1199346879.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4743254-wall-street-breakfast-podcast-taiwan-semi-chips-in-big-gains", "pub_date": "2024-12-10 14:49:10"}]}